An improvement to make this function more efficient is to use a single pass through the list to simultaneously find both the minimum and maximum values, reducing the time complexity from O(n log n) to O(n). Here's the improved code:
```python
# Improved version
def find_max_difference(nums):
    if len(nums) < 2:
        return None
    min_val = max_val = nums[0]
    for num in nums[1:]:
        if num < min_val:
            min_val = num
        elif num > max_val:
            max_val = num
    return max_val - min_val
