Find and fix the bug in the following code snippet. The function `processData` is supposed to read a file, parse its contents, and store the parsed data into a dynamically allocated array of structures. The structure `Record` contains an integer `id` and a string `data`. The function should handle file reading errors, memory allocation errors, and parsing errors. Fix the bug so that the function correctly handles all possible errors and cleans up resources appropriately.

